SOLD

Here's a nice old Ithaca Model 37 in 12 gauge. It has a 30" full choke barrel and the desirable corn-cob forend. The wood is in good condition with normal wear, and a mark on the right side of the butt stock. It has not been sanded or refinished. It has the original Ithaca butt plate and it a nice, honest, old Ithaca.

The bottom-eject on these Ithacas make them appealing to both right- and left-handed shooters. title: For Sale:  FR Jung & Sohne 1800's 16ga SxS Double BBL Shotgun
postcontent:
I recently picked up this C&R shotgun at a firearms auction. I had a friend of mine, who's an antique gun collector, look at it and give me some information. It's from Suhl, Germany made in the mid 1800's. The inscription between the barrels says FR. JUNG u. SOHNE in Suhl. Inside the break it also says RIEDER, and has a number of markings. This gun is very ornate, with a lot of decorative engravings (too many to picture), including two doe, a buck, mule deer, bore, fox, and a hound. Because of the animals, we are guessing it was made for someone in the US. It also has a horn grip, carved cheek-pad, engraved side plates and hammers, a spring-door compartment in the stock with engraved door/cover, and the barrels have a design on them (fading near the end). This gun is absolutely beautiful, and in great condition for it's age. There are two things I noticed that need mentioning...first, near the end of the forearm, both sides have broken pieces (the tip of the forearm is fine), and one of the decorative screws is missing from the stock-compartment door that holds a piece of leather to keep the shells from making noise inside the stock (see pictures). My friend told me these screws were commonly used in many guns of that era, so would probably be very easy to find and replace. These are 16 Gauge Side by Side Damascus Barrels, the lenght is about 30.5", and the overall weight is about 5.5 lbs. I have taken a number of pictures to show condition and markings, and can email more if you are SERIOUSLY interested. If you have any questions I will do my best to answer. This gun does not requre an FFL so I can ship it directly to you.

I believe this is the best upper available. This has all the dimensional perfection and strength of a good billet upper. Yet it fits perfectly on standard lowers. It is reinforced for extra strength, ideal for ensuring accuracy on rifles with optics. 

This is almost identical to the Noveske MUR that is selling for at least $100 more. 

Payment options are as easy as I can make them. Paypal personal gift is free. Credit card and regular Paypal transactions carry a 3% fee. 

Manufacturer info: 

MUR at a glance: 

Construction 7075 aircraft-grade aluminum forging. Prior to machining, the forging is fully stress relieved; heat treated, aged twice and undergoes a proprietary cryogenic treatment. Compatibility Fits all AR-type lower receivers made to Milspec standards. Will fit all select-fire AR-15/M16/M4 rifles and carbines. Will fit most of the semi-auto AR-type lower receivers (currently available). Weight MUR-1A (with assist) weighs less than 10 oz. The MUR-1S (shell deflector only) weighs less than 8 oz. Dimensions Height of rail (from the centerline of the bore): 1.215”. Color/Finish Black matte (anti-reflection/glare) Hard coat anodized (Type-III, Class 2). Bore’s surface in coated with dry film lube, over the anodized surface. Special Features Improved strength over conventional forged “flat-top” upper receivers. Stronger than any “billet” upper receiver with similar material and dimensional characteristics. Tighter manufacturing tolerances, when compared to the competition. The Modular Upper Receiver (MUR) is a rigid MilSpec flat-top upper receiver made to fit all AR15/M16/M4 rifles and carbines. The MUR was developed to give the customer a MilSpec correct upper receiver with a thicker wall, making the MUR upper receiver a stronger platform. This more rigid upper receiver will increase accuracy and reliability, while extending the life of the interfacing components, such as the bolt carrier group and barrel assembly. MUR-1A (with bolt assist) showing the right side. Mounted to the MUR-1A is a CASV-S rail/handguard system. The MUR comes in two models: one with Bolt-Assist/Shell-Deflector (part# MUR-1A) and the second with Shell Deflector only (part# MUR-1S). Vltor offers the selection at the time of purchase, but does not offer a service to exchange the Bolt Assist or Shell Deflector. The MUR is made from a 7075 aircraft-grade aluminum forging. Prior to machining, the forging is fully stress relieved, heat treated, aged twice and undergoes a proprietary cryogenic treatment. The MUR is precision machined and each part finished by hand. There is not a better upper receiver available. The main benefit of the MUR is that it is dimensionally correct. Vltor ensures the reliability and accuracy of our production process by using precision machining equipment, thorough quality control inspections, and a 100% final check of all critical dimensions. When you own a Vltor MUR, you have the highest quality upper receiver available on the market today. All MURs feature a MilStd-1913 scope mounting rail and come equipped with an Ejection-Port, Dust Cover Door.

postcontent:
Here's a really nice S&W Model 28-2 in a factory box. The gun is in excellent condition. The box is in very nice condition. The date of manufacture is 1966.

There is a story behind this gun. I bought this gun from a lady in Montana who told me that it belonged to her uncle. Her uncle was a bank manager and he bought the gun new and kept it in the drawer of his desk, loaded. When he retired, he took the gun out and shot the six rounds that were in it, cleaned it, and put it away. The box contains five empty casings, along with the original tools that came with the gun. The only mark on the gun is on one sport on the cylinder where it seems that it might have come from being in a wood desk drawer and is shown in the third photo.

Now, the serial number on the box is S 271180. The serial number on the gun is S 275277. The numbers are very close. I have no reason to believe the lady would lie about the gun so my guess would be that when the gun was purchased it was put into the wrong box. In any case, the gun is in excellent condition, and the box and contents are very nice.

Package price = $1500 firm.    No shipping.

To ship rifle and magazines only = $1600 Shipped.  Will not ship to states where they are restricted.

Rifle alone, $1100.  

Would entertain trade for AR-15  or  Glock 9mm pistols Gen 3 or Gen 4
